Write a Java 8 program to check if two strings are anagrams or not using the stream API and lambda expressions.


Traditional Code:

import java.util.Arrays;

public class Demo {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        char[] arr1 = "listen".toCharArray();
        char[] arr2 = "silent".toCharArray();

        Arrays.sort(arr1);
        Arrays.sort(arr2);

        if(Arrays.equals(arr1, arr2)){
            System.out.println("is Anagram");
        }else{
            System.out.println("is not Anagram");
        }
    }
}


O/P:
is Anagram


Java 8:

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.stream.Collectors;

public class Demo {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        String str1 = "listen";
        String str2 = "silent";

        String join1 = Arrays.stream(str1.split("")).sorted().collect(Collectors.joining(""));

        String join2 = Arrays.stream(str2.split("")).sorted().collect(Collectors.joining(""));

        if(join1.equals(join2)){
            System.out.println("is Anagram");
        }else{
            System.out.println("is not Anagram");
        }
    }
}


O/P:

is Anagram

